modules.description: Provides functions for reading from and writing to C-like structures using Bigarray, enabling direct memory manipulation. Works with byte sequences and structured data layouts represented as arrays. Used to parse and generate binary protocols, such as network packets or file formats.

Converts Cstruct buffers and values to and from s-expressions, enabling serialization and deserialization of binary data. Accepts raw memory buffers and Cstruct.t instances, producing or reconstructing them from structured sexp formats. Used to persist or transmit binary content in a textual, structured format.
